      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "The full spectrum of biophysical and functional assays should ideally be collected from all samples, thus allowing for a sweeping assessment and the application of computational approaches to the entire cohort. While admittedly it is not always feasible or practical to collect entire data sets from large cohorts, estimating smaller sample sizes for reliable analysis should be carefully considered prior to experimental data collection, as this can be influenced by multiple factors, including the computational methods applied and dimensionality of the data (e.g. number antibody features and functions) [CITATION_1] ."
